<TopicLayout slug="self-worth">
  <p class="lede">Where does my worth come from?</p>
  <p>
    Is it in strength? beauty? intellect? athleticism? money? Is your worth rooted in any of these? If it is,
    it's a fleeting worth. A very fragile worth indeed. One car accident can remove every one of these
    identities in an instant. Then what value would you be?
  </p>
  <p>
    No, thanks be to God, our worth is one declared outside of ourselves, independent of humanity, and secure
    far beyond the reaches of the status quo.
  </p>
  <p>
    Your worth is one declared and set by your Creator, the One who made you. He began making your worth known
    when after five days of speaking all of creation into being. He paused to take time on you, humanity. He
    formed us with His own hands, made us in His own image, gave life to us with His own breath, and when His
    justice called for our due punishment, He redeemed us with His own blood.
    <br />
    A beautiful statement of worth,
    <br />
    I'd say!
  </p>
  <p>
    This statement wasn't made because we are special, valuable or worthy of it. Our value has nothing to do
    with us and quite everything to do with him. He loves the unlovable, forgives the unforgiveable, values the
    unvaluable, declares worth over the unworthy.
  </p>
  <p>
    You see, our worth is established by something outside of ourselves and completely unreliant on ourselves
    or anybody else. Our worth is determined and held secure by the Indestructible Being that sustains all
    life. His price tag on us is one of unfathomable cost.
    <br />
    The problem is do we know it?
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      ...The heart of the wicked is of little value (Proverbs 10:20)
      <br />
      <b>And yet...</b>
      <br />
      ...at just the right time, when we were still powerless, Christ died for the ungodly. Very rarely
      will anyone die for a righteous person, though for a good person someone might possibly dare to die. But
      God demonstrates his own love for us in this: While we were still sinners, Christ died for us. (Romans
      5:6-8)
      <br />
      <b>We are the valueless wicked hearts that are valued.</b>
    </li>
    <li>
      For God so loved the world that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him shall not
      perish but have eternal life. - John 3:16
    </li>
    <li>
      Are not five sparrows sold for two pennies? Yet not one of them is forgotten by God. Indeed, the very
      hairs of your head are all numbered. Don't be afraid; you are worth more than many sparrows. - Luke
      12:6-7
    </li>
    <li>
      So God created mankind in his own image, in the image of God he created them; male and female he created
      them. -
      <a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/GEN.1.1-31" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Genesis 1:27</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      For you created my inmost being; you knit me together in my mother's womb. I praise you because I am
      fearfully and wonderfully made; your works are wonderful, I know that full well. My frame was not hidden
      from you when I was made in the secret place, when I was woven together in the depths of the earth. Your
      eyes saw my unformed body; all the days ordained for me were written in your book before one of them
      came to be. - Psalms 139:13-16
    </li>
  </ul>
</TopicLayout>
